o where gating is a realistic option. Basically, it means that you're abandoning your friends. In a place like Chardok/Hate etc., etc., etc. where you have to fight your way there, it means that after the CR they are still going to be without you because you can't get to the party location solo (had to go in with them).<br>
<br>
Frankly, it's a spell slot you should be using to help your raid survive rather than die.<br>
<br>
Now, please don't take this as meaning to be harsh on folks. I'm merely stating it as my firm belief on how gate classes should be approaching a raid scenario. Unlike a group scenario where gating out may mean you have someone left to do the CR for you later and arrange (or actually perform) rezzes, someone who has gated out rarely has much to offer a raid force because of group location. The risk/reward ratio is just not there. It's a live and learn thing. I've seen this issue with accidental gating in like 4 of the last 5 raids that I've partcipated in and/or heard about. In three cases it's had a significant impact on a wipe out. Staying there may not have prevented the wipe out (actually, in two cases, it almost certainly would have prevented it), but it sharply decreased the chance of survival.<br>
<br>
When raiding - you're in it together. Fact is, plan on dying. If you don't, that's terrific, but you should prepare yourself for it mentally. Raid encounters are TOUGH - that's why they are raid level encounters. Especially when a group first starts raiding together (and learning how the raid and each other work), wipeouts are part of the game. For some classes, death is just plain part of the game (if you ever do Rumblecrush, for example, most any raid plan fully expects the intial slower to die - it's just plain planned for because it's a very high likelihood).<br>
<br>
You go in, you take your lumps. I have to deal with this as a bard in some instances too. My resists are keeping folks alive. I sit there and wait for that heal to come in, and, even if it doesn't, I stay there until the very end because that extra 5 or 10 seconds of resists is keeping the rest of my group (heck, could be the whole raid once I get my AoE's) alive, and that extra few moments of them getting damage may mean everything to the raid. My rez will come in due course. If it's still a wipeout, well, I gave it my best shot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub135.ezboard.com/bexodusfellowshipforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kamdarentilzha>Kamdar Entilzha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1109<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(2/10/03 9:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1075.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.exodusfellowship.com/Kam_small2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Funny...</span><hr size=1> I remember a time when Cobo took some pretty hard lumps cuz he didn't have Gate ready!  I guess the times they are a-changin'  As we get older and bolder, anyway.<br>
