<br>
When and if there's gonna be a WIPE OUT, there always is one LURKING about. Having the cleric camp out when all is lost, enchanter down, TANK's defensive buying you the time to camp. The other warriors are taking on MOBs, camp out if you can. Sometimes you won't be able too. DA yourself and sit down and camp out. Have a monk pull and FD MOBS away if you can.<br>
<br>
The thing about a WIPE OUT is you should expect one if your raiding. Things go WRONG, a fizzle CH spell, TANKS's going down to FAST and no backup healer. The means to get back up and going for what you came for as FAST as possible is what everyone is looking for. If you ported to Timbuckto and people have to wait for you, you're slowing down the game. YES it was SLOWN DOWN from the WIPE OUT but everyone is ready to go now and full mana but we're waiting on you to get back down here to Call of the Hero your BUTT. TIME means respawns and that's what your fighting against.<br>
<br>
Chardok's a MEAN place and HARD to get to the King and Queen if you have a WIPE OUT. A Necro is a must for camping the KING and QUEEN. A MAGE is NICE for Call of the Hero to get people that come late.<br>
<br>
There's also a thing called taking one for the group. You have AGGRO on a MOB, it can't be taken off of you for some reason. Giving the group time to take down a first MOB and YES dying yourself can save a group from that DREADED PING PONG effect. So long as the clerics alive you can get REZed back in. Downing one MOB can make or break a RAID. I know I've been there many times, hopefully I've learned to MEZ or if my MEZ can MEZ that MOB by now.<br>
<br>
The BEST FUN I've ever had was on WIPE OUTS, you learn so much and GAIN so much on them. How to fight the MOB and what not to do the next time your there. RAGE, Chardok, Kael, HOT, Plane of Storms, and the Plane of Justice Trials have been some of the GREATEST experiences of my TOONS LIFE.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :dance --><img src=http://www.bakkerij.torfs.easynet.be/emoticons/dans.gif ALT=":dance"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
