<br>
When people make mistakes, I usually make sure they know what they did wrong, and suggest a way that may work better next time.  I DO NOT come down on people, or get all bent out of shape.  Why?  It's not fun.  It's a game, and I think it's all-important to ALWAYS focus on that.  Hell, it's even #8 in our bylaws.  <br>
<br>
Other people may run their raids/guilds any way they feel is best.<br>
<br>
As for listening, the #1 problem is not that people don't listen, its that people WHO AREN'T IN CHARGE give contradictory orders.  This is usually one of the more experienced players that believes they know best.  And they may, but it's not their job to give orders - send a tell to the RL.<br>
<br>
We're getting there, guys.  Relax, smile, laugh it off, try again.  I had a lot of fun during the wipeout in Chardok on Sat.<br>
